# Code ownership — required reviewers per file path.
#
# Why these paths and not others:
#  - supabase/migrations/  — schema changes are where 90% of future bugs
#                            originate. Every migration must be reviewed
#                            by the project owner before merge.
#  - lib/operations/        — the drafts pipeline + warnings + matcher.
#                            One bug here corrupts the entire data flow;
#                            changes need explicit owner sign-off.
#  - .github/workflows/     — the CI gate itself. Letting any contributor
#                            relax thresholds undoes the protection.
#  - .github/CODEOWNERS     — the meta: don't let CODEOWNERS itself drift.
#  - docs/operations/       — operational runbooks. Stale runbooks are a
#                            real outage vector.
#
# Format: <pattern> <space> @owner [@owner2 ...]
# Last matching pattern wins; keep the file ordered narrow → broad.

# Schema changes
supabase/migrations/   @beber88

# Core operations logic
lib/operations/        @beber88

# CI + meta
.github/workflows/     @beber88
.github/CODEOWNERS     @beber88
.github/pull_request_template.md  @beber88

# Operational documentation
docs/operations/       @beber88
docs/development/      @beber88
